{"TopicId":175289,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to handle gravity?","CreatedByName":"Martini","CreatedById":189185,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T02:24:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Martini","CreatedById":189185,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T02:24:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cpre dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border:none;color:#212121;font-size:16px;padding:0px .14em 0px 0px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003EHello, I was working on a project and it would be very useful to be able to\nset the gravity on the kerbin surface at something close to 2.5G\nSo it\u0027s possible or it\u0027s crazy? \n\nSorry for the possible errors: I do not know how to speak English.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T02:45:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t speak to if it\u0027s crazy or not \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EHowever, it\u0027s not that hard if you don\u0027t mind modding your game and rolling up your sleeves for some light config editing.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6907968011\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/140580-143-kopernicus-release-2-may-6/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:226px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T07:17:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t Alt-F12, hack gravity, set to 2.5x be easier?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T08:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223385856\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175289\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527232647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t Alt-F12, hack gravity, set to 2.5x be easier?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepends on the situation. \u0022Hack gravity\u0022 will influence the whole universe, Kopernicus can do the change to a single body.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, testing something like a surface base in a separate save file -\u0026gt; hack gravity is the way you go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPermanent change -\u0026gt; Kopernicus\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martini","CreatedById":189185,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T10:50:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cpre dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border:none;color:#212121;font-size:16px;padding:0px .14em 0px 0px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003EWhen I select hack gravity the game just reduces the G force, but I want to increase\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T11:28:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, you should be able to push the \u0022hack gravity\u0022 slider up to 10G. If this doesn\u0027t work for you, you can still try kopernicus with an config file like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n@Kopernicus:AFTER[Kopernicus]\n{\n    @Body[Kerbin] \n    {\n        @Properties\n        {            \n            geeASL = 2.5\n        }\n    }\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-25T12:16:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSir, hyperedit. Works like charm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}